1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,280
If you bring us proof
of Mrs. Mookmanee's crimes,

2
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,560
we'll reward you

3
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,720
as much as you want.

4
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:50,360
Can your secretary be trusted?

5
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:52,840
No one would ever betray my money.

6
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:55,200
And what if Trai
didn't use money to lure him?

7
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,120
This won't be enough to bring me down.

8
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,200
Who said this was all?

9
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,120
Excuse me.

10
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,480
Mom!

11
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:10,880
<i>I'm going to use</i>
<i>that arrogant little rich girl</i>

12
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,120
<i>to get revenge on Trai</i>

13
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,920
and deal with Pakbung for you.

14
00:03:15,040 --> 00:03:16,520
What is Rut going to do to Pakbung?

15
00:03:16,600 --> 00:03:17,400
Look.

16
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:20,320
Your daughter is about to become
a murderer in front of the whole world.

17
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,760
Bowing to my feet now is too late.
Do you hear me?

18
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,880
Huh?

19
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,480
Hey. No, please.

20
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:24,280
Mika. Mika. Mika.

21
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,760
Mika.

22
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:31,440
Mika…

23
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,520
Mika, get up. Don't lie here.

24
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:37,160
Mika, the ground is dirty. Get up.

25
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,160
Mika…

26
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:44,560
Mika, don't lie here.

27
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,520
No, not like this!

28
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,040
Excuse me.

29
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:24,680
Let's go.

30
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:51,600
Look.

31
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:52,560
3 MITI NEWS BY KITTI SINGHAPAT

32
00:05:52,640 --> 00:05:53,560
Mrs. Mook tried to flee,

33
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:55,360
so the court revoked her bail.

34
00:05:55,440 --> 00:05:57,280
She's now being held in prison.

35
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:01,120
If she manages to escape again,

36
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:04,480
I swear I'll bring three-colored cloth
and incense to make an offering.

37
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,840
What kind of person
is more powerful than the law?

38
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:10,840
A rich one. Have you ever seen
a rich person stay in jail?

39
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,840
Honestly, jail isn't even enough.

40
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,960
She should've been executed.

41
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:18,240
Hey, easy. Be gentle right now.

42
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:21,280
Yeah. I warned you to tone it down.

43
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:24,520
See?
Violence never leads to anything good.

44
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,280
Mrs. Mook passed that violence
to her daughter. And see?

45
00:06:28,400 --> 00:06:31,960
She deserved it. Death is the only thing
that can knock down the rich.

46
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,760
I understand you're angry, Samlee.

47
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:38,400
But maybe, try to forgive them.

48
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:40,520
Mika is already dead.

49
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:41,520
And Mrs. Mook

50
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:45,160
can't even attend her daughter's funeral.

51
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:58,200
Eat something.

52
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,360
Or you'll get sick too.

53
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,560
I can't.

54
00:07:09,520 --> 00:07:11,400
If you can't eat, then…

55
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,760
Drink this.

56
00:07:23,080 --> 00:07:25,800
Just drink a little. Please.

57
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:46,560
The doctor said Kanah's stable.

58
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,040
He just needs rest.

59
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:51,600
He's been asleep since last night.

60
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,960
Why isn't he awake yet?

61
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,800
He's not even a heavy sleeper.

62
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:00,040
He should wake up now.

63
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,080
Why is he still sleeping?

64
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,720
Can't I be lazy for once?

65
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:11,400
Kanah!

66
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,400
Kanah, you're awake!

67
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:21,400
- Kanah.
- Ouch, Bung.

68
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:28,120
You little brat. You scared me to death.

69
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,640
You're okay, right?

70
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,000
Yeah.

71
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:35,159
I'm okay. Nothing serious.

72
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:39,559
What about Dad? How is he?

73
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,360
He lost a lot of blood.

74
00:09:08,360 --> 00:09:10,840
During the surgery to extract the bullet,

75
00:09:11,880 --> 00:09:13,560
he almost didn't make it…

76
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:18,240
The doctor said
we have to monitor him day by day.

77
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,840
He's still unconscious.

78
00:09:22,280 --> 00:09:23,600
Pakbung.

79
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,640
Can I believe Dad this time?

80
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,840
That he really did it for us,

81
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,760
because he truly loves us?

82
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:41,280
I don't care what he lied about before.

83
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:45,160
I just want him to be safe.

84
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:52,400
I do too. I want him to come back.

85
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:06,120
Dad's going to be okay, right?

86
00:10:16,720 --> 00:10:17,600
Dad.

87
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:28,000
His blood pressure is dropping.
Please step outside first.

88
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:47,280
Mr. Trai, if Dad…

89
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,280
He'll be fine.

90
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:51,280
But I'm scared.

91
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,600
How is my dad?

92
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:01,520
He's out of danger now.

93
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,840
He's regained consciousness.

94
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,280
Thank you, Doctor.

95
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:09,360
Sure.

96
00:11:13,760 --> 00:11:14,760
Bung.

97
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:17,600
Kanah.

98
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,800
I told you. He'll be fine.

99
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,960
Welcome home, Uncle.

100
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:47,960
May all your troubles be gone.

101
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:48,840
Yay!

102
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,320
Oh, Kanah,

103
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:53,240
should we help him lie down?
I cleaned everything.

104
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,160
Sure.

105
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,760
- Wait.
- Uncle, wait.

106
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,240
I've been lying down for a month.
I'm done lying down.

107
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,640
Then go sit on the sofa, Dad.

108
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:04,080
- Oh, then, take your shoes off, Uncle.
- Slowly, Uncle.

109
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:05,240
Put them away.

110
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,320
- Oh.
- Walk slowly. Be careful.

111
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:08,760
- Don't pull him.
- Be careful.

112
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,800
- I know!
- Hey.

113
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:11,840
- Uncle, watch your step.
- It won't hurt.

114
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,360
- You can walk.
- Easy, Uncle.

115
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,800
- Dad, be careful.
- Alright,

116
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,480
- Kanah, get out.
- Stay away.

117
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:19,480
Uncle, wait.
Let me dust off the sofa first.

118
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:22,280
- Yeah. Lean back.
- Yeah.

119
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:24,560
- Yes, like that.
- Uncle.

120
00:12:24,640 --> 00:12:26,640
- Hold the pillow.
- I'm holding it.

121
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:29,080
Uncle, are you hungry? Kanah said you have

122
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:31,840
to eat a soft diet, so we made soup.

123
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,760
Oh. Soup?

124
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:35,720
You still haven't talked to your dad yet?

125
00:12:38,240 --> 00:12:39,240
Of course I have.

126
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,720
I was at the hospital the whole time.
How couldn't I?

127
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,920
No. I mean, to clear things up.

128
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:49,560
What you said while he was unconscious,

129
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:50,960
you should tell him.

130
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:58,040
I took care of him every day.
He should know how I feel.

131
00:13:04,240 --> 00:13:07,280
Say it while you still can.

132
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:49,400
Wait, wait. Where are you going?

133
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,080
What do you want to do?

134
00:13:51,680 --> 00:13:53,560
Just tell me. I'll get it for you.

135
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:58,320
I'm going to the bathroom.

136
00:13:59,440 --> 00:14:02,120
- Dad, I'll take you.
- Uh.

137
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:04,360
It's alright.

138
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,640
The bathroom is right there.
I can go by myself.

139
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:10,240
I won't

140
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:13,200
bother you two.

141
00:14:14,040 --> 00:14:15,080
- Bother?
- Bother?

142
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:32,560
‪Dad.

143
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,440
Someone like me…

144
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:44,560
doesn't deserve this.

145
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:48,560
Deserve what?

146
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,000
What do you mean?

147
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,960
You,

148
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,600
Kanah,

149
00:15:00,640 --> 00:15:02,880
and

150
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,680
everyone taking care of me like this.

151
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,160
It's too good.

152
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,960
It's too good

153
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,440
for a bad person like me.

154
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:18,440
Oh, Dad, don't say that.

155
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:26,680
I was so scared you'd die,

156
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:32,720
so scared I forgot everything you did.

157
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:45,120
I forgot that I was mad at you,

158
00:15:45,800 --> 00:15:47,320
that you made me upset.

159
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:50,880
I just knew

160
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:53,840
I wanted you to live.

161
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,280
Pakbung…

162
00:16:01,680 --> 00:16:02,560
Dad.

163
00:16:03,840 --> 00:16:05,520
Don't leave us again.

164
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:22,160
Stay with us a long time, Dad.

165
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:37,800
Kanah, Pakbung,

166
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:40,160
I swear on my life.

167
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:45,520
I'll be a good father for you.

168
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,560
I won't hurt

169
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,240
you both again.

170
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:56,560
I don't know about other people,
but I believe you.

171
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,160
Dad.

172
00:17:05,280 --> 00:17:07,119
I love you.

173
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,640
- What?
- What?

174
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,000
I love him more.

175
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:18,000
That's not true. I love him more.

176
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:22,800
Come here. I love him more.

177
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:25,119
- Dad, hug me.
- No.

178
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,599
Be gentle, Kanah.

179
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,920
I know.

180
00:17:29,960 --> 00:17:31,760
I love you the most, Dad.

181
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,840
I love you too.

182
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:37,080
Thank you.

183
00:17:38,240 --> 00:17:40,080
I won't let you go anywhere again.

184
00:17:41,040 --> 00:17:42,120
- I won't go.
- Stay with me.

185
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,040
I won't go anywhere.

186
00:17:50,040 --> 00:17:51,840
I have so much I want to tell you, Dad.

187
00:17:54,160 --> 00:17:55,360
But I don't have that chance anymore.

188
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,080
I miss you.

189
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:09,800
Whoa, Rachen.

190
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:13,200
Please, next time, make some noise or
something. My heart just skipped a beat.

191
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,200
I saw you were having a moment.

192
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:19,720
You okay now?

193
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,880
Hold on. Alright, I'm okay now.

194
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,240
What is it?

195
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:29,200
If Dad were still here,
what would you want to tell him?

196
00:18:30,840 --> 00:18:32,080
A lot.

197
00:18:34,120 --> 00:18:36,840
But the most important thing
I'd want to say is…

198
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,080
Thank you, Dad.

199
00:18:47,120 --> 00:18:49,280
Thank you for giving me a big brother.

200
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:58,120
Yeah, I'm probably not good
at this. I'm gonna go shower.

201
00:18:58,200 --> 00:19:00,720
Normally, you'd follow up
with something annoying.

202
00:19:01,680 --> 00:19:03,720
I'm not used to this version of you.

203
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:08,760
When are you coming back to run Be Rich?

204
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:13,960
Whoa, what? So the second I'm gone,
it's a mess? You miss me?

205
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:16,240
It's worse than a mess.

206
00:19:16,320 --> 00:19:18,760
The news about you,
Mrs. Mookmanee's situation,

207
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:20,560
everything's chaos.

208
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,640
You should come back and help me already.

209
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,560
Are you begging me?

210
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:28,640
Mr. Chairman is begging me
to come back and help?

211
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,720
Because Be Rich is yours.

212
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:37,040
The company is ours.

213
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:40,360
I'll come back and help you for sure.

214
00:19:40,440 --> 00:19:42,640
But first, I need to find Rut.

215
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:45,200
Ever since Mrs. Mookmanee got arrested,
he disappeared.

216
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:47,680
Rut's not going to just vanish.

217
00:19:47,760 --> 00:19:50,320
He'll find a way to come after us.

218
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:52,480
Then we attack him first.

219
00:19:54,320 --> 00:19:58,480
If he hates money so much,
we'll use money to deal with him.

220
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,440
Your food's ready.

221
00:20:08,880 --> 00:20:10,680
<i>Mr. Rut Rueangwichan</i>

222
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:13,360
<i>has an arrest warrant</i>
<i>for multiple murder cases</i>

223
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:14,600
<i>and is currently on the run.</i>

224
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:17,840
<i>If you spot him and provide information,</i>

225
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:20,200
<i>I'll reward you immediately in cash,</i>

226
00:20:20,280 --> 00:20:21,520
<i>100,000 baht.</i>

227
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:24,680
<i>You can add the Line account on screen</i>
<i>and send the information right away.</i>

228
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:27,920
<i>And if he is found within 24 hours,</i>

229
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,560
<i>I will add</i>
<i>another 100,000 baht immediately.</i>

230
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:34,440
Whoa, another 100,000?

231
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:36,320
That's 200,000 total.

232
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,360
Wow, that's a lot.

233
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,920
‪It's 100,000?

234
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:58,120
Please wait a moment.

235
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:01,520
Hey, Kim, customer's here.
It's your turn. Are you going or not?

236
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:02,800
If not, I will.

237
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,200
Yeah, yeah, one sec.

238
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,120
Please wait a moment.

239
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:17,920
Rachen, you bastard.
You think I'm only worth 200,000?

240
00:21:19,080 --> 00:21:20,880
You're looking down on me.

241
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:23,480
You think your money is God or what?

242
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:27,920
You Bowornmongkolphong bastards.
You won't have a damn thing left.

243
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:36,960
Ow, ow, Bung, move! Hot, hot!

244
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,320
Why aren't you wearing gloves?

245
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,640
I'm too lazy.

246
00:21:42,240 --> 00:21:44,600
How can you be lazy? They're right there.

247
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:46,760
Yeah, I'm just lazy.

248
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:48,440
- Hey.
- Why?

249
00:21:48,520 --> 00:21:50,320
- I only brought it this far.
- Did it burn your hands?

250
00:21:50,400 --> 00:21:51,880
- Did it?
- It's fine.

251
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:52,800
Hey, hey.

252
00:21:52,880 --> 00:21:54,720
Are you two arguing again?

253
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:57,520
We're not arguing, Dad. We're

254
00:21:57,600 --> 00:22:00,760
exchanging perspectives.

255
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:03,800
Hey. Exchanging what perspectives?

256
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:07,040
Dad, Kanah's so stubborn.

257
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:08,920
He never listens.

258
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:09,840
What?

259
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:12,280
- Hey, hey.
- Wait, Pakbung.

260
00:22:13,560 --> 00:22:14,680
If you do that, I won't get to eat.

261
00:22:14,760 --> 00:22:15,920
Yeah.

262
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:18,360
Come on, come on. Right here.

263
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:22,840
Oh, the ladle.

264
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,400
Mr. Trai isn't coming?

265
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:34,760
I'm here.

266
00:22:35,840 --> 00:22:37,480
Whoa, Trai.

267
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:39,280
Speak of the devil.

268
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:41,080
The moment we talk about you, you show up.

269
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,800
Sorry, I got held up with some work.

270
00:22:45,800 --> 00:22:47,400
I brought you bubble tea.

271
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,400
There's some for you and Kanah too.

272
00:22:51,480 --> 00:22:54,640
I got cold-pressed juice as well.
I'll pour it into glasses.

273
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:59,720
Wow, you're so smooth.
Why don't you just move in already?

274
00:23:02,080 --> 00:23:05,880
Or Mr. Trai, why don't you take
Pakbung in to live with you?

275
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:07,120
So you won't have to go back and forth.

276
00:23:08,080 --> 00:23:08,960
Wow. Well…

277
00:23:09,040 --> 00:23:13,200
Both options sound pretty interesting.
But I can't decide on my own.

278
00:23:15,760 --> 00:23:17,000
So? What do you say?

279
00:23:17,600 --> 00:23:19,000
What do you say, Pakbung?

280
00:23:27,840 --> 00:23:31,040
Let's eat before it gets cold. Come on.

281
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,120
Hurry.

282
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:39,400
Chopsticks. Help set the table.

283
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:08,960
It's okay. I've got it.

284
00:24:16,440 --> 00:24:17,440
But…

285
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,880
Why don’t you just say yes
to Mr. Trai already?

286
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:22,760
You don't believe in him?

287
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:24,800
I do.

288
00:24:28,480 --> 00:24:30,120
The problem is me.

289
00:24:33,440 --> 00:24:35,360
Mr. Trai is really, really good.

290
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:38,200
Sometimes, I even wonder

291
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:42,600
what I did in a past life
to deserve meeting him.

292
00:24:43,360 --> 00:24:44,440
He makes me feel safe

293
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:46,600
and comfortable.

294
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:49,520
He's so good that I'm scared.

295
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,840
If one day he disappears,

296
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:54,440
will I be able to handle it?

297
00:24:55,360 --> 00:24:56,840
Where would Mr. Trai go?

298
00:24:58,080 --> 00:24:59,320
One way or another,

299
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,000
we all lose people.

300
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:04,760
If not by separation, then by death.

301
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:07,960
Having someone and then they're gone,

302
00:25:08,960 --> 00:25:11,920
that's scarier than
never having them in the first place, Dad.

303
00:25:12,520 --> 00:25:15,560
You're afraid of loss
because of me, aren't you?

304
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:21,720
How many times have I made you feel hurt?

305
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:29,120
I don't know. I stopped counting.

306
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,760
Too many to count, right?

307
00:25:35,320 --> 00:25:37,000
But can I ask you for one thing?

308
00:25:38,160 --> 00:25:40,120
Don't let your past pain

309
00:25:40,200 --> 00:25:42,720
destroy your future.

310
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:45,720
Don't let a terrible father like me

311
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:48,920
ruin the rest of your life.

312
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:51,520
If Mr. Trai is good,

313
00:25:52,720 --> 00:25:54,400
then hold on to him.

314
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:57,040
It doesn't have to be forever,

315
00:25:59,040 --> 00:26:00,480
just as long as you can.

316
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:05,360
Love as long as you can.
Be happy as long as you can.

317
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:07,840
I want to see my daughter

318
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,440
live with confidence.

319
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:12,960
Don't fear anything.

320
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:17,040
Loss and pain

321
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:20,280
are normal.

322
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:22,400
So why be afraid of something normal?

323
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,200
Dad.

324
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,720
You're so cool.

325
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,480
It's like, suddenly,

326
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:33,680
there's this flash of light
hitting my face like whoosh.

327
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:36,240
You're not being sarcastic, right?

328
00:26:36,320 --> 00:26:38,280
I'm serious.

329
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:41,200
What you said was really good.

330
00:26:50,560 --> 00:26:53,840
Thank you for snapping me back.

331
00:26:56,400 --> 00:26:57,480
My girl…

332
00:27:04,560 --> 00:27:06,000
You don't need to be afraid anymore.

333
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:15,040
Keep it up.

334
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:16,760
Keep it up.

335
00:27:16,840 --> 00:27:18,600
That's how you do it.

336
00:27:19,800 --> 00:27:21,480
- Like this?
- That's right.

337
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:28,560
Don't be afraid of pain.

338
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:31,400
It's normal.

339
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:37,960
You're this good.

340
00:27:38,840 --> 00:27:40,320
How could I let you go?

341
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:44,760
I'm gonna get you.

342
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:24,560
You finished work already?

343
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:28,280
I hit my target today, so I got off early.

344
00:28:32,520 --> 00:28:33,560
Hey, Mr. Trai.

345
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:36,880
I haven't told you yet, right?

346
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:39,360
Last night,
I opened up and talked to my dad.

347
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,400
About what?

348
00:28:41,840 --> 00:28:42,680
About you.

349
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,280
About me?

350
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:47,000
Well?

351
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:55,720
- Hey, hey.
- Uh, Mr. Trai,

352
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:59,120
there are… there are parents here
to tour the school before deciding.

353
00:28:59,840 --> 00:29:01,040
How should I welcome them?

354
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:03,840
They're our first parents ever.
I'm nervous.

355
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:06,840
Hey, hey, calm down. I'll handle it.

356
00:29:07,440 --> 00:29:08,400
Really?

357
00:29:09,040 --> 00:29:09,880
Okay.

358
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:14,440
Ready?

359
00:29:14,520 --> 00:29:15,360
Of course.

360
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:20,880
Here.

361
00:29:21,680 --> 00:29:22,520
Let's go.

362
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:27,920
Hey. Let's go.

363
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:35,120
Thank you so much.
See you at the start of the semester.

364
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:37,280
I'll walk you out.

365
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:44,400
This way, please.

366
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:53,560
Mr. Trai.

367
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:55,440
First parents, first student.

368
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:57,720
What do we do?
Should we celebrate right now?

369
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:00,440
First, go change your clothes.

370
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:02,200
They're gonna think I'm a mafia boss.

371
00:30:02,800 --> 00:30:03,960
Aren't you a mafia boss?

372
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,160
I'll hit you in the head.

373
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:07,040
I'll go change right now.

374
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:15,360
So, where were we?

375
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,480
You said you talked to your dad, about…

376
00:30:18,320 --> 00:30:19,240
You remembered?

377
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:22,080
Of course. It's about us.

378
00:30:22,880 --> 00:30:24,400
My dad said

379
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,720
he wants me to be confident

380
00:30:26,800 --> 00:30:28,880
and not be afraid of anything.

381
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:34,120
And I think it's time that we…

382
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,800
Mr. Trai. Mr. Trai.

383
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,280
Someone called in a tip about Rut.

384
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:03,920
It's just holding hands.

385
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,440
Why is it so hard, huh?

386
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:12,360
Here! We're holding your hand.
It's not that hard.

387
00:31:12,440 --> 00:31:13,280
Yeah.

388
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,160
No.

389
00:31:15,880 --> 00:31:17,800
I wanted to hold Mr. Trai's hand,

390
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:20,040
but the timing kept getting messed up.

391
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:24,160
Oh. So you want it to feel romantic?
Just the two of you,

392
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:27,920
all sweet and cuddly, like,
"You have me, I have you" vibe?

393
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:30,360
Not that dramatic.

394
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:32,320
I just

395
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,800
want him to know that I'm ready.

396
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:37,360
Ready for what?

397
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:41,560
Ready to have a husband, right?

398
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:46,320
- Really?
- Samlee.

399
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:48,160
Niuniu.

400
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:50,640
Right?

401
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:54,080
- Hey, hey.
- He's here.

402
00:31:54,160 --> 00:31:55,360
Tell him.

403
00:32:04,960 --> 00:32:06,960
Oh, Samlee, Niuniu, you're here too?

404
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:10,160
- What's with the fit?
- What are you wearing?

405
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:11,800
Isn't it cool?

406
00:32:11,880 --> 00:32:13,440
No.

407
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:15,320
It's not. What is that?

408
00:32:24,360 --> 00:32:28,000
- Mr. Trai, Pakbung wants to--
- Hey, hey.

409
00:32:30,720 --> 00:32:32,120
So, what about Rut?

410
00:32:34,680 --> 00:32:37,480
I had someone follow the lead, but…

411
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:38,400
it wasn't Rut.

412
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:41,040
Oh. Too bad.

413
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:42,320
Pakbung.

414
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,800
Why are you covering her mouth?
What were you gonna say?

415
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:47,760
Samlee was gonna say Pakbung wants a hu--

416
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:52,200
Why are you covering Niuniu's mouth?

417
00:32:52,280 --> 00:32:55,560
Whoa, Mr. Trai, this is super suspicious.
Both hands too.

418
00:32:57,880 --> 00:32:59,080
Pakbung wants a--

419
00:32:59,160 --> 00:33:00,320
No!

420
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:05,520
I don't know anymore!

421
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:11,840
She's shy.

422
00:33:14,080 --> 00:33:16,480
Fine, just skip holding hands.

423
00:33:22,760 --> 00:33:24,080
Running away again?

424
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:26,800
No.

425
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,640
There's no one here.

426
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:33,240
If you want to do something to me,

427
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:35,760
go ahead.

428
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:39,520
Who wants to do anything to you?

429
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,280
I don't want to do anything.

430
00:33:44,280 --> 00:33:47,200
Didn't your dad tell you to be confident?
To not be afraid of anything?

431
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,840
I'm not afraid.

432
00:33:51,480 --> 00:33:53,040
I'm just shy.

433
00:33:55,200 --> 00:33:56,040
Shy?

434
00:33:59,680 --> 00:34:01,320
If you're shy, I'll close my eyes.

435
00:34:03,600 --> 00:34:05,440
I'd rather look into your eyes.

436
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:07,320
You want to look into my eyes?

437
00:34:11,040 --> 00:34:13,639
No, open your eyes.

438
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,760
Now step back. Two steps.

439
00:34:24,480 --> 00:34:25,880
One, two.

440
00:34:27,440 --> 00:34:28,280
Good?

441
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:32,400
I'm starting.

442
00:34:33,760 --> 00:34:35,440
I'll only say this once.

443
00:34:37,920 --> 00:34:38,800
Mr. Trai,

444
00:34:41,719 --> 00:34:43,239
you once told me

445
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:45,960
we'd hold hands

446
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:48,440
on the day I reached out to you first.

447
00:34:49,280 --> 00:34:50,600
I think…

448
00:34:52,159 --> 00:34:53,400
I'm ready.

449
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:06,240
I want to hold your hand

450
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,520
and stay by your side

451
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,840
for as long as I can.

452
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:16,200
Are you ready to walk with me?

453
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:23,360
I've been waiting
for this moment my whole life.

454
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:25,520
How could I not be ready?

455
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:32,760
Hey, hey.

456
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:38,400
Hey.

457
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,840
Mr. Trai!

458
00:35:41,920 --> 00:35:45,760
SAENG DAO KINDERGARTEN

459
00:35:56,120 --> 00:35:57,280
Stop.

460
00:35:58,000 --> 00:35:59,560
Stop right there.

461
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:01,240
No teasing, no mocking,

462
00:36:01,320 --> 00:36:03,120
and don't tell Kanah either.

463
00:36:08,160 --> 00:36:12,360
I can't. I'm gonna explode.

464
00:36:12,440 --> 00:36:13,680
Hey.

465
00:36:14,480 --> 00:36:16,560
Are you ready to walk with me?

466
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:22,360
I've been waiting for this moment
my whole life. How could I not be ready?

467
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:31,840
So what's the next step?

468
00:36:31,920 --> 00:36:34,360
Will you get married right away?
So I can prepare properly.

469
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:38,480
Should we just register our marriage now?

470
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:41,000
Isn't that too soon?

471
00:36:42,720 --> 00:36:44,960
But I'm free tomorrow.

472
00:36:47,320 --> 00:36:48,800
Oh, hey.

473
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:52,240
Mr. Trai, something happened at Be Rich.

474
00:37:05,200 --> 00:37:07,440
Our customers'
personal info database got hacked.

475
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:10,040
Names, addresses, IDs,
everything important.

476
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:14,000
We should inform our customers right away,
not let it drag until tomorrow.

477
00:37:14,080 --> 00:37:16,480
Trai, can't you see
we're rushing to recover the data?

478
00:37:17,920 --> 00:37:20,080
Most organizations that get hit
with ransomware

479
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:22,200
can't recover their data, Bro.

480
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:25,640
But announcing it right now
isn't good for Be Rich either.

481
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:29,680
Exactly. The company's already in
a bad situation and has a lot of crises.

482
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:31,480
If the media finds out

483
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:34,480
that a lending company that's supposed
to be trustworthy like Be Rich

484
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:37,120
let customers' sensitive data leak,

485
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,160
won't we be screwed?

486
00:37:40,480 --> 00:37:41,600
Mr. Trai,

487
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:43,640
the hacker sent a message.

488
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:52,240
They're threatening to keep
releasing customer data bit by bit

489
00:37:53,080 --> 00:37:54,760
if we don't pay them 100 million baht.

490
00:37:57,080 --> 00:37:59,760
100 million? Are they insane?

491
00:38:02,000 --> 00:38:03,760
They've already released the first batch.

492
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:08,840
<i>Breaking news. Be Rich Leasing,</i>

493
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:11,600
<i>which was hit by a cyberattack yesterday,</i>

494
00:38:11,680 --> 00:38:14,320
<i>has now had</i>
<i>its customers' personal data leaked.</i>

495
00:38:14,400 --> 00:38:16,600
<i>Names, addresses, national ID numbers,</i>

496
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:18,960
<i>even bank accounts.</i>

497
00:38:19,040 --> 00:38:21,440
<i>Over 10,000 customers have been exposed…</i>

498
00:38:22,640 --> 00:38:25,200
Why does Be Rich have
nothing but problems lately?

499
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:27,840
It has to be Rut.

500
00:38:37,200 --> 00:38:39,880
INCOMING CALL

501
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:51,440
<i>Don't you dare turn it off.</i>

502
00:38:52,120 --> 00:38:55,200
<i>You've seen the news about Be Rich,</i>
<i>haven't you? It was me.</i>

503
00:38:55,280 --> 00:38:57,320
<i>I demanded 100 million from them.</i>

504
00:38:58,080 --> 00:39:00,600
<i>You want to be rich, don't you, Darin?</i>

505
00:39:00,680 --> 00:39:02,480
<i>Work with me.</i>

506
00:39:03,320 --> 00:39:04,160
No!

507
00:39:04,680 --> 00:39:05,600
TURN OFF

508
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,560
- Da.
- No.

509
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:10,680
What's wrong?

510
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:17,760
Mom.

511
00:39:19,040 --> 00:39:22,680
<i>Darin! Why did you turn it off?</i>
<i>Are you trying to run from me?</i>

512
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:27,760
Da, what's wrong? Da.

513
00:39:27,840 --> 00:39:30,680
Rut's gone crazy.
I can't do this anymore, Mom.

514
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:33,680
- Calm down.
- I can't take it anymore.

515
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:35,120
Calm down.

516
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:36,960
Calm down.

517
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:01,560
The Be Rich data hack
was Rut's doing. He texted me himself.

518
00:40:12,240 --> 00:40:16,440
If I pretend to cooperate with him,
Trai will be able to catch him, right?

519
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,520
What do you mean?

520
00:40:19,160 --> 00:40:21,240
You'll cooperate with Rut to trap him,

521
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,920
then let Mr. Trai arrest him?

522
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:27,920
Yes. I already offered it to Trai before,
but he didn't care.

523
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:30,840
Then, you should listen to Mr. Trai.

524
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:34,240
Rut's gone insane. He won't stop.

525
00:40:35,200 --> 00:40:37,840
Your life with Trai will never be peaceful

526
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,520
if you let him roam free like this.

527
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:45,040
You think I'm here to trick you, Pakbung?

528
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:47,040
You've done it before.

529
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:51,560
Yes.

530
00:40:52,440 --> 00:40:53,600
I did.

531
00:40:53,680 --> 00:40:56,000
But my life has kept sinking
lower and lower.

532
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:58,480
I'm done.

533
00:41:00,360 --> 00:41:02,400
I really want to start over.

534
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:07,840
If you won't help me talk to Trai,
that's fine.

535
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:10,600
I'll find my own way.

536
00:41:29,160 --> 00:41:30,120
Ms. Darin.

537
00:41:34,960 --> 00:41:35,960
Let's work together.

538
00:42:11,080 --> 00:42:12,720
Rut must be behind this.

539
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:14,840
Even if we pay the 100 million,
he'll never stop.

540
00:42:14,920 --> 00:42:16,440
We have to find him.

541
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:22,000
Mr. Trai, look at this file.

542
00:42:25,480 --> 00:42:28,320
I tried digging through Be Rich's system,

543
00:42:28,400 --> 00:42:31,360
seeing if there was any way
to recover the data.

544
00:42:31,440 --> 00:42:35,240
And I found a file Tritot hid.
It's named "Trai"

545
00:42:35,320 --> 00:42:37,640
but I can't access it.
It needs a password.

546
00:42:37,720 --> 00:42:40,800
If it's named after you, then
the password should be related to you.

547
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,480
I tried everything.

548
00:42:42,560 --> 00:42:45,120
Birthday, phone number,

549
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:47,760
national ID, nothing worked.

550
00:42:49,560 --> 00:42:50,600
Then what could the password be?

551
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:56,200
- Mom.
- What?

552
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,280
Mom.

553
00:43:01,040 --> 00:43:02,800
Mom?

554
00:43:02,880 --> 00:43:04,400
Did you say "Mom"?

555
00:43:05,160 --> 00:43:06,400
Mom?

556
00:43:07,280 --> 00:43:09,960
Mom? Mom's birthday?

557
00:43:17,640 --> 00:43:19,160
Try the year in AD, sir.

558
00:43:19,760 --> 00:43:20,680
AD?

559
00:43:28,920 --> 00:43:29,760
Hey.

560
00:43:32,160 --> 00:43:33,040
Hey.

561
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:38,000
Prarop, download every file onto my phone.

562
00:43:38,080 --> 00:43:39,120
Yes, sir.

563
00:44:14,520 --> 00:44:16,200
PLEASE USE THE PASSENGER ELEVATOR AS USUAL

564
00:44:22,480 --> 00:44:25,360
It's not so serious that you have
to pull out your shares.

565
00:44:25,440 --> 00:44:26,960
Please calm down.

566
00:44:27,040 --> 00:44:29,240
I can handle it. You don't need to worry.

567
00:44:31,280 --> 00:44:32,560
Rachen.

568
00:44:33,880 --> 00:44:35,320
Are you really gonna give Rut money?

569
00:44:35,400 --> 00:44:39,040
Not all of it. But right now,
we need to buy time, don't we?

570
00:44:39,120 --> 00:44:41,520
It's not just the customers
who don't trust us anymore.

571
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:44,640
Shareholders, executives,
they're all about to ditch us.

572
00:44:44,720 --> 00:44:46,480
Then help me look at this.

573
00:44:46,560 --> 00:44:48,320
I found an old clip Dad kept.

574
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:59,160
INCOMING VIDEO CALL
UNKNOWN

575
00:45:04,600 --> 00:45:07,000
<i>Hi. You miss me, don't you?</i>

576
00:45:07,080 --> 00:45:08,920
I knew it had to be you.

577
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:10,840
Yeah, it's me.

578
00:45:12,640 --> 00:45:16,360
Looks like you really missed me,
even put a 200,000 bounty on me.

579
00:45:17,680 --> 00:45:18,680
So?

580
00:45:19,800 --> 00:45:21,560
How was the customer data I leaked?

581
00:45:21,640 --> 00:45:23,960
It was a huge batch. Are you impressed?

582
00:45:24,480 --> 00:45:26,400
You think you can run from me?

583
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:29,240
I'll be the one dragging you down myself.

584
00:45:29,320 --> 00:45:33,040
Lee, he's in our building.

585
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:35,520
- I'll check right now which room he's in.
- Go.

586
00:45:37,480 --> 00:45:38,800
Hey, Trai.

587
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:40,880
Are you gonna let
your brother keep yapping

588
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:42,520
and not say hi to me?

589
00:45:43,120 --> 00:45:44,080
<i>You miss me?</i>

590
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:47,560
Look. See who I'm with.

591
00:45:56,360 --> 00:45:57,320
Pakbung?!

592
00:45:58,880 --> 00:46:00,680
Not just your new girl, you know.

593
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:02,600
Here.

594
00:46:03,680 --> 00:46:05,920
Your ex is here too.

595
00:46:07,360 --> 00:46:09,800
Honestly, I didn't even want to kill her.

596
00:46:11,240 --> 00:46:12,800
But she tried to stab me in the back.

597
00:46:12,880 --> 00:46:15,160
Rut, calm down.

598
00:46:15,240 --> 00:46:16,840
You want money, don't you?

599
00:46:17,680 --> 00:46:21,280
Here, 100 million.
I prepared it for you already.

600
00:46:25,000 --> 00:46:26,920
Maybe 100 million is not enough anymore.

601
00:46:27,440 --> 00:46:29,840
I've got these two with me.
I should get more than that.

602
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:31,760
How much do you want? Say it.

603
00:46:31,840 --> 00:46:34,400
And what do you think they're worth?

604
00:46:38,920 --> 00:46:40,400
As much as your life?

605
00:46:42,920 --> 00:46:46,040
If you love them that much,
then trade your life for theirs.

606
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:02,080
Prarop, go clear the building.

607
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:03,120
Yes, sir.

608
00:47:07,680 --> 00:47:09,320
This way, please.

609
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:11,240
Run, run.

610
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:13,880
Hurry. Keep moving.

611
00:47:13,960 --> 00:47:16,520
Hurry. This way.

612
00:47:16,600 --> 00:47:19,000
Hurry. This way. Run.

613
00:47:19,080 --> 00:47:20,040
Hurry.

614
00:47:21,000 --> 00:47:23,080
Run, run. Hurry.

615
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:25,840
- Hurry.
- Run.

616
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:42,200
They know I'm here.

617
00:47:46,520 --> 00:47:48,160
That makes it fun.

618
00:47:49,600 --> 00:47:52,880
Come on. Come on. Come on.

619
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:55,280
Come on. Bring it on!

620
00:47:57,520 --> 00:47:59,400
<i>I've got a gift for you too, Rut.</i>

621
00:48:07,040 --> 00:48:10,440
<i>Rut, I have something to tell you.</i>

622
00:48:11,560 --> 00:48:15,920
<i>At first, I planned to tell you</i>
<i>after everything was over,</i>

623
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:19,360
<i>but Mr. Tritot wanted me</i>
<i>to leave this message</i>

624
00:48:19,440 --> 00:48:23,400
<i>in case something happened,</i>
<i>so you wouldn't misunderstand.</i>

625
00:48:23,480 --> 00:48:26,520
<i>About the case where Mr. Trai's girlfriend</i>
<i>hit someone with a car,</i>

626
00:48:26,600 --> 00:48:29,480
I was the one who begged Mr. Tritot

627
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:31,640
to pin all the blame on me.

628
00:48:32,520 --> 00:48:33,400
Huh?

629
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:35,400
<i>Mr. Tritot didn't agree at all.</i>

630
00:48:35,480 --> 00:48:37,200
But I…

631
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:40,560
I wanted money.

632
00:48:42,680 --> 00:48:43,760
That's not true.

633
00:48:43,840 --> 00:48:47,280
<i>I didn't dare tell you</i>
<i>because I was afraid you'd stop me.</i>

634
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:50,520
<i>Please don't be mad at me, Rut.</i>
<i>Try to understand me.</i>

635
00:48:50,600 --> 00:48:53,280
<i>I feel guilty every time</i>
<i>I see you trying so hard.</i>

636
00:48:53,880 --> 00:48:56,560
<i>You had to work twice, three times</i>

637
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:58,120
<i>harder than everyone else.</i>

638
00:48:59,320 --> 00:49:01,440
<i>Sometimes, you lost good opportunities</i>

639
00:49:02,320 --> 00:49:05,920
<i>because I couldn't afford</i>
<i>to give you a good education.</i>

640
00:49:07,760 --> 00:49:09,880
<i>The more I think about it,</i>
<i>the more guilty I feel.</i>

641
00:49:10,800 --> 00:49:13,440
No, Dad, it's not your fault.

642
00:49:18,560 --> 00:49:21,600
Ms. Darin. Ms. Darin.

643
00:49:21,680 --> 00:49:24,200
<i>I wanted to be a good father to you.</i>

644
00:49:24,280 --> 00:49:28,040
And this was the only way
I could do something for you.

645
00:49:40,440 --> 00:49:41,760
Be quiet.

646
00:49:46,880 --> 00:49:48,480
Hey.

647
00:49:51,880 --> 00:49:52,960
No, Dad.

648
00:49:53,480 --> 00:49:55,920
I needed you more than I needed money.

649
00:49:57,080 --> 00:49:59,000
Why would you go to prison for me?

650
00:50:00,400 --> 00:50:01,960
What do we do?

651
00:50:05,720 --> 00:50:06,560
Untie the rope first.

652
00:50:10,080 --> 00:50:13,680
<i>Not much longer, Son.</i>
<i>Once everything is done,</i>

653
00:50:14,240 --> 00:50:15,840
<i>we'll be together again.</i>

654
00:50:16,680 --> 00:50:18,320
<i>We'll eat together again.</i>

655
00:50:18,400 --> 00:50:22,080
<i>Don't forget to prepare shrimp paste dip</i>
<i>with grilled catfish for me.</i>

656
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:24,680
You have to live a better life than mine.

657
00:50:24,760 --> 00:50:26,520
<i>I don't want anything.</i>

658
00:50:27,240 --> 00:50:29,360
<i>I just want you to be happy.</i>

659
00:50:30,440 --> 00:50:31,840
I love you, Rut.

660
00:50:35,280 --> 00:50:39,120
I love you, Dad. I love you. I love you.

661
00:51:00,880 --> 00:51:01,920
Run!

662
00:51:04,520 --> 00:51:05,400
Pakbung!

663
00:51:06,360 --> 00:51:08,400
Found them. Hallway, 19th floor.

664
00:51:11,320 --> 00:51:12,360
Nineteenth floor?

665
00:51:18,320 --> 00:51:19,200
Hey.

666
00:51:19,960 --> 00:51:22,160
Come on. Can you walk?

667
00:51:22,240 --> 00:51:23,800
He'll catch us. Get up.

668
00:51:25,600 --> 00:51:27,040
Go.

669
00:51:35,680 --> 00:51:37,200
Where do you think you're going?

670
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:39,240
Ms. Darin.

671
00:51:39,320 --> 00:51:42,200
Pakbung, run! Run!

672
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:54,440
Run.

673
00:51:55,160 --> 00:51:56,760
Pakbung, run.

674
00:51:57,600 --> 00:51:58,480
Go.

675
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:04,760
Come on.

676
00:52:26,080 --> 00:52:27,040
Da!

677
00:52:29,800 --> 00:52:31,160
Trai.

678
00:52:31,240 --> 00:52:34,080
Pakbung… Go help Pakbung.

679
00:52:35,720 --> 00:52:37,040
- Lee, stay with Da.
- Yes, sir.

680
00:52:46,840 --> 00:52:50,480
Why are you always kidnapping me?

681
00:52:50,560 --> 00:52:54,920
Just because I'm Mr. Trai's girlfriend,
I have to be the victim every single time?

682
00:53:01,320 --> 00:53:05,400
Even if I die, nothing will change.

683
00:53:06,400 --> 00:53:08,880
Mr. Trai will just get a new girlfriend.

684
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:12,120
Let me go. Please.

685
00:53:12,200 --> 00:53:14,240
Don't underestimate yourself.

686
00:53:14,320 --> 00:53:17,000
Trai's way more obsessed
with you than you think.

687
00:53:17,080 --> 00:53:18,280
You don't believe me?

688
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:20,800
Then wait until he arrives.

689
00:53:22,240 --> 00:53:24,120
Wait for that bastard Trai to show up.

690
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:27,160
And then I'll blow you up.

691
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:29,640
Both your hearts will merge together.

692
00:53:31,560 --> 00:53:32,760
So damn romantic.

693
00:53:32,840 --> 00:53:34,960
Your dad might think it's romantic!

694
00:53:35,960 --> 00:53:37,600
Oh, my dad? My dad?

695
00:53:41,840 --> 00:53:44,040
Like your dad?

696
00:53:44,120 --> 00:53:45,160
Rut!

697
00:53:48,760 --> 00:53:49,760
So disappointing.

698
00:53:49,840 --> 00:53:51,760
Trai should've been
the one to come up first.

699
00:53:52,440 --> 00:53:55,160
You want money, don't you? Take it.

700
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:56,280
Here.

701
00:53:57,200 --> 00:53:59,240
This can give you a new life.

702
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:01,560
Take it and let Pakbung go!

703
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:04,360
You're trying to steal
your brother's girl again?

704
00:54:06,360 --> 00:54:08,640
You love Be Rich to death.

705
00:54:08,720 --> 00:54:11,320
Why risk it this time for a woman?

706
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:33,960
Not coming at me now?

707
00:54:49,400 --> 00:54:50,240
Mr. Trai…

708
00:55:01,680 --> 00:55:04,080
Didn't you see the video
your dad recorded, Rut?

709
00:55:04,720 --> 00:55:07,760
Your dad volunteered to take the fall.
You can't blame me and my dad.

710
00:55:07,840 --> 00:55:10,120
No. It's because of your money.

711
00:55:10,200 --> 00:55:12,000
It's because you're rotten to the core,
you bastard!

712
00:55:13,360 --> 00:55:16,440
No!

713
00:55:18,240 --> 00:55:21,720
Mr. Trai, help. The bomb.

714
00:55:50,880 --> 00:55:53,480
- Hey, hey, calm down. Look at me.
- I'm scared.

715
00:55:53,560 --> 00:55:55,280
- I'm here, okay?
- I'm scared.

716
00:55:55,360 --> 00:55:58,240
You're alright. I'm right here.

717
00:56:06,240 --> 00:56:09,720
You're okay now. You're okay, alright?

718
00:56:09,800 --> 00:56:12,680
- Alright?
- I'm scared. Help me.

719
00:56:16,440 --> 00:56:19,760
Couple of the year. We have to celebrate.

720
00:56:22,080 --> 00:56:23,560
No…

721
00:56:23,640 --> 00:56:24,960
- No.
- Don't, Rut, don't!

722
00:56:26,120 --> 00:56:27,400
Don't!

723
00:56:27,480 --> 00:56:28,600
Don't!

724
00:56:28,680 --> 00:56:30,760
- Hey!
- Hey!

725
00:56:38,840 --> 00:56:40,880
Take it off. Take it off.

726
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:42,840
Lift your foot up.

727
00:56:44,760 --> 00:56:46,720
Don't. Don't!

728
00:56:51,240 --> 00:56:52,200
Damn it!

729
00:56:57,000 --> 00:56:58,040
Mr. Trai.

730
00:57:00,720 --> 00:57:02,240
Who first? Who first?

731
00:57:02,320 --> 00:57:04,440
Big brother or little brother? Or her?

732
00:57:05,040 --> 00:57:06,160
Who first? Answer me!

733
00:57:09,520 --> 00:57:12,360
Answer me. Answer me.

734
00:57:12,440 --> 00:57:14,560
Answer me. Anyone, answer me!

735
00:57:14,640 --> 00:57:15,960
- Freeze!
- This way, Officers.

736
00:57:16,040 --> 00:57:16,920
Drop the weapon and put your hands up!

737
00:57:19,160 --> 00:57:21,040
Why would you come so fast?

738
00:57:21,760 --> 00:57:23,000
Rut, that's enough. Enough!

739
00:57:23,080 --> 00:57:23,920
Not enough!

740
00:57:24,000 --> 00:57:26,680
Hey, Rut. Think it through.

741
00:57:26,760 --> 00:57:29,280
If you shoot us, you're dead.
You won't get away.

742
00:57:29,360 --> 00:57:30,320
Yeah?

743
00:57:30,880 --> 00:57:33,800
I'll die? Well, I'm not going
to prison anyway.

744
00:57:33,880 --> 00:57:36,640
I'm not losing to your money.
I'm not losing to you.

745
00:57:47,560 --> 00:57:48,520
Close your eyes.

746
00:57:48,600 --> 00:57:50,240
Hey, I'm here. I'm here.

747
00:58:16,680 --> 00:58:19,240
You're this cute.
You deserve a prize, don't you think?

748
00:58:19,320 --> 00:58:24,240
With a sweet vibe like this,
shouldn't we do something?

749
00:58:24,320 --> 00:58:25,320
Propose!

750
00:58:25,400 --> 00:58:29,160
- Do it! Do it!
- Do it! Do it!

751
00:58:29,240 --> 00:58:30,800
I do want to marry you, Pakbung.

752
00:58:34,280 --> 00:58:35,160
But not now.

753
00:58:36,320 --> 00:58:38,720
- You didn't want to get married anyway.
- I do!

754
00:58:38,800 --> 00:58:40,560
- Huh? What was that?
- Huh? What was that?

755
00:58:40,640 --> 00:58:42,640
- I want to get married!
- Huh?!

756
00:58:42,720 --> 00:58:44,920
This is the cake
the hotel prepared for you.

757
00:58:45,520 --> 00:58:47,000
And this is the proposal card.

758
00:58:47,080 --> 00:58:48,560
Pakbung. Pakbung.

759
00:58:48,640 --> 00:58:50,480
Hey? What do we do?

760
00:58:54,400 --> 00:58:56,640
The board members approved my plan.

761
00:58:56,720 --> 00:58:58,920
Don't forget the shares you promised me.

762
00:58:59,000 --> 00:59:00,400
When did I ever promise you that?

763
00:59:01,000 --> 00:59:02,160
Are you cheating me?

764
00:59:02,240 --> 00:59:03,640
What can you do?

765
00:59:03,720 --> 00:59:04,960
You bastard!

766
00:59:53,120 --> 00:59:56,600
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
